What this means in plain English:

✓ You CAN use cc-forge for your own projects (personal or commercial)
✓ You CAN modify it and adapt it for your needs
✓ You CAN contribute back improvements via pull requests
✓ You CAN share it with others

✗ You CANNOT resell cc-forge itself as a product or service
✗ You CANNOT white-label it and charge for access to the framework
✗ You CANNOT build a paid SDLC consultancy product on top of it
  without written permission from the author

The distinction: using cc-forge to build YOUR product is permitted.
Selling cc-forge itself (or a lightly rebranded version of it) is not.

